DESCRIPTION

ann.py is a Python code with a purpose of creating Artificial Neural Network 
(ANN)model. The ANN is used to predict outputs based on known input. The model 
used a Feed-Forward Neural Network type and a Back-Propagating (Multi-Layered 
Perceptron (MLP)) algorithm. The usage of this is knowing the ANN Architecture, 
the Model Loss of training and validation based on Epoch, the weight of nodes, 
and the biases. The generated model is evaluated based on Root Mean Squared 
Error (RMSE), relative error, squared error, and Coefficient of Determination 
(R^2) in respect to the predicted and actual testing data.

Data suitable for this are:
* 2 (two) files of training data and testing data already divided
  For splitting a dataset, see splitter.py
* Files with comma separated value (.csv) or Ms Excel 2003-365 (.xlsx) extension
* Table or matrix data with regular rows and columns of uniform size
* Table with 1 line of header and then lines (or rows) of data
* Data with numerical values

PRE-REQUISITES

The code has been tested on numerous devices ranging in operating system, 
environment, and parameter. Before using the code, user have to install 
pre-requisite libraries: pandas, openpyxl, pydot, scikit-learn, tensorflow, 
numpy, matplotlib, tabulate, and colorama.

To install these libraries at once, execute the command on 
Windows Command Prompt (cmd) or Linux / MacOS Terminal :

    > pip install pandas openpyxl pydot scikit-learn tensorflow numpy matplotlib tabulate colorama

